		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName><sic>Pittsburg</sic></placeName> <date>August 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1852</date></p>
			<p>to the <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Dear sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)">I take the liberty to communicate<lb/> to you the proceedings of our last meeting &#40;yesterday&#41; Kahl Staray&#61;<lb/>themajim<add>&#63;</add> <persName>Mr A. Fink</persName> has been elected <sic>Presitent</sic>. <persName role="author">N. Gallinger</persName> secret.<lb/> <persName>I. Morgenstern</persName> Tres. By this meeting all our members &#40;except two<lb/> have not been present&#41; by their own free will bound themself<lb/> to <sic>atent</sic> regular divine service Every <date>Shabath</date> &#38; Holy days or<lb/> be fined one dollar for each missing&#44; as our Kohl has been<lb/> <sic>organist</sic> nearly five years but has not <sic>ingreased</sic> we only<lb/> number 15 members and have a <sic>yerly</sic> expense of about 450 Dollars<lb/> but still we get along so far <sic>exept</sic> could very seldom get<lb/> minian on <date>Shabath</date> but now by our determination with the<lb/> help of God will have regular services on all <sic>occations</sic> <persName>Mr. Salshath<add>&#63;</add></persName><lb/> is our chasan shodet &#38; teacher we have a burring Ground and<lb/> have a fine <sic>larg</sic> &#38; <sic>compfortibel</sic> Rooms two <add>Hebrew</add> one belongs to<lb/> Kohl and the room well <sic>fixt</sic> up for our <sic>Sinagoge</sic> we have<lb/> only 14 members although <sic>ther</sic> are over thirty Jewish Families<lb/> in this city <sic>ther</sic> is a other Kohl here <sic>wich</sic> calls themselves Polish<lb/> they have as I can judge about 8 or 9 members they would<lb/> not join use because we <sic>wand</sic> them to pay as much<lb/> towards the expenses as the members of our Kohl pay but<lb/> we got along so far and I hope we will get along further<lb/> we have <sic>severall</sic> Polish members in our Kohl&#44; they the Polish Kohl have <sic>injourd</sic><lb/> us and tried to insure us <del>for</del> since they are here on<lb/> every <date>rosh hasona</date> &#38; <date>Kipur</date> <sic>the</sic> have <sic>organised</sic> a minian<lb/> for <sic>themsef</sic> and <del>got</del> trid all means to get every stranger<lb/> away from our <sic>sinagoge</sic></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p>last year they came to us and rented some <sic>pewes</sic> in our<lb/> <sic>sinagoge</sic> and then <sic>dit</sic> not come nor pay for them but<lb/> we let them alone and do as they please</p>
			<p>I would have wrote you before but as I am a very<lb/> poor English <sic>schollar</sic> I was <sic>allways</sic> <sic>ashaimed</sic> to do so<lb/> with your permission I will keep you advised of every<lb/> <sic>importied</sic> thing <sic>wath</sic> belongs to our <sic>relition</sic> and comes<lb/> to my notice here if you can <sic>mak</sic> out my writings<lb/> and <sic>mening</sic></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">I remain dear sir yours</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">N. Gallinger</persName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
